@startuml
title SafeReport - Full System Test Case with Anonymous Reporting and Admin Review

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ArrowColor #1F4E79
skinparam DefaultFontName Arial
skinparam DefaultFontSize 12

skinparam activity {
  BackgroundColor #F7FBFF
  BorderColor #1F4E79
  FontColor #16324F
  StartColor #2E7D32
  EndColor #2E7D32
  DiamondBackgroundColor #FFF4D6
  DiamondBorderColor #C58A00
  BarColor #1F4E79
}

skinparam swimlane {
  BorderColor #9BB3C9
  TitleBackgroundColor #FCFEFF
  TitleFontColor #16324F
}

|Admin|
start

:Log in to MUST Admin Portal;
:Upload or update official contacts;
:Upload or update policy knowledge base;
:Open dashboard and reports queue;

|Reporter|
:Open SafeReport welcome screen;
:Choose Continue with Account\nor Continue Anonymously;

|System|
if (Continue with Account?) then (Yes)
  :Show login and registration flow;
  |Reporter|
  :Register account or log in\nby email or phone;
  |System|
  :Create or validate Firebase Auth account;
  :Initialize notification service;
  :Load user home dashboard;
else (No)
  :Show anonymous quick info form;
  |Reporter|
  :Provide role, gender,\nand optional faculty/department;
  |System|
  :Store anonymous session context;
  :Load anonymous home dashboard;
endif

|Reporter|
:Open AI Support Assistant\nor Support Services;
:Request guidance, contacts,\nor emergency help;

|System|
:Load chatbot runtime config;
:Load policy knowledge and official contacts;
:Start secure support session;
note right
  If crisis or high-risk language is detected,
  the chatbot can raise an alert and direct
  the reporter to emergency support options.
end note

|Support Services|
:Provide counseling, legal,\nmedical, and emergency resources;
:Allow phone call or SMS launch\nfor urgent assistance;

|Reporter|
:Open Report Incident form;
:Select incident type(s);
:Enter description, date, time,\nlocation, perpetrator, witnesses,\nand complainant response;
:Attach photo, video,\nor audio evidence;
:Confirm incident location;
:Tap Submit Report;

|System|
:Validate form and internet connectivity;
if (Anonymous submission?) then (Yes)
  :Check anonymous device submission limit;
  :Generate tracking token;
  note right
    Anonymous submissions are limited per device.
    The current build allows up to 2 anonymous
    reports before requiring account sign-in.
  end note
endif
:Upload images to ImgBB;
:Upload videos and audio to Cloudinary;
if (Some evidence uploads fail?) then (Yes)
  |Reporter|
  :Choose Cancel or Submit Anyway;
  |System|
endif
:Create reports record in Firestore;
:Set report status = pending;
:Store evidence URLs, timestamps,\nanonymity flag, and report metadata;

if (Anonymous report?) then (Yes)
  :Display tracking token dialog;
else (No)
  :Show success message;
  :Enable My Reports and Notifications access;
endif

|Reporter|
if (Anonymous reporter?) then (Yes)
  :Open Track Anonymous Report;
  :Enter saved tracking token;
  |System|
  :Look up report by tracking token;
  :Show anonymous report status summary;
else (No)
  :Open My Reports;
  :Search, filter, and open report details;
  :Optionally edit report\nor add more evidence;
endif

|Admin|
:Open Reports Management;
:Filter by status, faculty,\ndepartment, role, date, or anonymity;
:Open report details;
:Assign case to reviewer,\ncommittee member, or admin;

|System|
:Save assignment metadata;
:Create process timeline entry;

|Admin|
:Review incident details,\nreporter profile, attachments,\nand AI insights;
:Move case through workflow\n<i>pending -> under_review -> investigating</i>;
note right
  Report workflow changes are role-based
  in the admin portal and are logged in the
  report process timeline.
end note
:Enter resolution message;
:Resolve or close report;

|System|
:Update status, stage,\naudit fields, and resolution details;
:Append process log entry;
if (Authenticated reporter?) then (Yes)
  :Create in-app notification record;
  :Refresh notifications and report details;
else (No)
  :Keep latest case status available\nthrough tracking token lookup;
endif

|Reporter|
if (Authenticated reporter?) then (Yes)
  :Open Notifications or My Reports;
  :Read status update and resolution message;
else (No)
  :Track case later using saved token;
endif
:Continue accessing support services if needed;

stop
@enduml
